  "description": "A bento-style hero that pairs an editorial content column with an asymmetric four-tile gallery, ideal for portfolios, hospitality brands, and lifestyle products that lead with imagery.",
  "descriptions": {
    "descriptive": "A 12-column split places the headline at lower-left and a four-tile bento gallery at right, with one tall feature image and three supporting cells in varied proportions. Captions float over photo corners on small chips, and tiles scale subtly on hover.",
    "usage": "Use as the homepage opener for studios, design agencies, hotels, restaurants, or boutique commerce sites where the work itself sells the brand. Pairs well with a stats strip below to anchor credibility before the user scrolls into project details.",
    "audienceFit": "Speaks to design-aware visitors who expect a portfolio-grade first impression — creative directors, hospitality managers, gallerists, and editorial commerce buyers."
